<bibRefCitation author="Bernhauer" box="[604,796,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1921) Zur Staphyliniden fauna von Sudamerika. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1921, 65 - 77." type="journal article" year="1921">Bernhauer, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Syntype deposited in FMNH (
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[1163,1372,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article" year="2012">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[1244,1304,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) (not examined).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[339,559,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hypotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andinus">
<emphasis box="[339,559,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Hypotelus andinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be easily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1337,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hypotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1224,1337,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Hypotelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the conspicuous, deep and large depression at the middle of the pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[949,1032,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[216,1355,230,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,157,1945]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Habitus, dorsal view. 9, Hypotelus insulanus, syntype, male; 10, H. praecox, lectotype, female; 11, H. scheerpeltzi sp. nov., holotype, male; 12, H. testaceus, syntype, male; 13, H. melanodelta sp. nov., holotype, female; 14, H. castaneus sp. nov., holotype, male; 15, H. brevitarsus sp. nov., holotype, male; 16, H. corniculatus sp. nov., holotype, female; 17, H. marginatus, syntype, male; 18, H. laevis, male; 19, H. andinus. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803652/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Redescription.</emphasis>
BL: 
<quantity box="[431,520,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="6.1">6.1 mm</quantity>
, BW: 
<quantity box="[592,681,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. Body slightly convex; dorsal surface matte, except elytra; entirely black with legs a little lighter (
<figureCitation box="[492,575,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[216,1355,230,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,157,1945]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Habitus, dorsal view. 9, Hypotelus insulanus, syntype, male; 10, H. praecox, lectotype, female; 11, H. scheerpeltzi sp. nov., holotype, male; 12, H. testaceus, syntype, male; 13, H. melanodelta sp. nov., holotype, female; 14, H. castaneus sp. nov., holotype, male; 15, H. brevitarsus sp. nov., holotype, male; 16, H. corniculatus sp. nov., holotype, female; 17, H. marginatus, syntype, male; 18, H. laevis, male; 19, H. andinus. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803652/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Dorsal integument of head and pronotum with fine punctures and granulate microsculpture; elytra each with one longitudinal finely punctate stria close to sutural margin, conspicuous only on basal half; metaventrite and abdomen with fine punctures and granulate microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis box="[199,334,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Male. Head</emphasis>
. With five moderately sized punctures with long setae on basal half of dorsal margin of eyes; supra-antennal area visibly prominent. Antennae almost reaching apex of elytra; every antennomeres with some dispersed long setae, setae on inner face are longest; antennomere 3 longer than 2; 5–11 gradually increasing in length toward antennal apex. Labrum with median third deeply emarginate, three pairs of long setae medially; lateral thirds with two pairs of long setae, two apical and two subapical. Mandibles symmetrical, one acute tooth on each inner margin. Mentum 2 times as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis box="[199,288,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum wider than long (PW/PL=1.25); anterior angles rounded and slightly prominent; apical twothirds with somewhat curved sides and basal one-third gradually narrowing toward the base; with complete internal mid-longitudinal ridge and conspicuous longitudinal median sulcus; conspicuous and deep large depression at middle. Elytra somewhat longer than wide (EL/BW=1.2), covering abdominal tergite 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis box="[199,312,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Apical abdominal segments 8 to 10 and genitalia were not studied, but according to 
<bibRefCitation pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
the shape of the structures are: sternite 8 with posterior margin truncate; tergite 9 with short ventral struts; tergite 10 with some long setae on apex and posterior margin with short fringes, basal half not divided longitudinally; sternite 9 with two pairs of long setae and truncate apex. Median lobe of aedeagus somewhat globose apex in lateral view, tube closed in dorsal view; length of parameres exceeds apex of median lobe by a little (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[203,400,980,1005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article" year="2012">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[278,326,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 248–250).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis box="[199,291,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Female.</emphasis>
Not examined. According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[623,835,1015,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[698,747,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
the female is similar to male except for: elytra a little shorter, covering only basal half of abdominal tergite 3; abdominal sternite 8 with pointed apex and short setae on posterior margin; tergite 10 divided longitudinally in basal half (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[966,1179,1087,1112]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article" year="2012">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[1046,1101,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 151); ovipositor consisting of a pair of weakly pigmented hemisternites and a pair of more apical coxites, and with many long setae on apex (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[298,495,1159,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article" year="2012">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[373,422,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 155). Spermatheca unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1563407727" country="Colombia" location="Beni" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Beni">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,467,1196,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Geographical records.</emphasis>
In the current study, the species was examined from 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1202,1196,1221]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1215,1436,1196,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" refString="Caron, E., Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. &amp; Newton, A. F. (2012) Cladistic analysis and revision of Piestus Gravenhorst with remarks on related genera (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Piestinae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 490 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10016" type="journal article">
Caron 
<emphasis box="[1293,1344,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
also recorded it from 
<collectingCountry box="[392,485,1231,1256]" name="Ecuador" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[540,623,1231,1256]" name="Bolivia" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[637,693,1231,1256]" country="Bolivia" name="Beni" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Beni</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation box="[716,813,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 114" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1701,1723]" captionTargetBox="[190,1375,215,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[150,1437,153,1679]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 114. Geographical records of Hypotelus. Hypotelus andinus, Colombia, Ecuador and Bolivia; H. insulanus, Caribbean islands; H. marginatus, Colombia, Venezuela and Guatemala; H. testaceus, Panama; H. brevitarsus sp. nov., Panama. Countries without dots but colored represent the occurrence but no locality given." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803674/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Fig. 114</figureCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1293]" box="[199,1024,1268,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,393,1268,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Biological notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[400,610,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hypotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andinus">
<emphasis box="[400,610,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Hypotelus andinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected in a Malaise trap.
</paragraph>
